{"version":1,"ops":[{"type":1,"author":{"id":"e6c152d440109efdc7afc4e9ac4ac193043f8f68"},"timestamp":1505722286,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUyNTgzOTgxOTY=","github-url":"https://github.com/letoram/arcan/issues/127","origin":"github"},"title":"(lwa) deadlock in crash recovery","message":"This is a fun one. In main connection crash recovery (and other uses of _migrate as its just like resize and drop, not thread safe), the hidden _drop/_migrate call chain may come from either an OpenAL thread performing a signal or from a queue or signal on the main thread, immediately causing the other to enter drop as well, causing a deadlock.\n\nThe actual solution to this is one is not entirely obvious and require testing/experiments outside this release window. The 'immediate' solution would be to extend the lock/unlock calls to annotate whether its safe or not to continue, but it requires an update to shmif/version bump so best to dwell on this one for a while as its not particularly severe.","files":null}]}